<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--secondary);margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;">Frequently Asked Questions about Drylining</h2>
<div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">What is drylining?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">Drylining is the process of fixing plasterboard to interior walls and ceilings without using wet plaster. It is faster, cleaner, and provides a smooth finish ready for decorating or painting.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">How long does drylining take?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">A typical room takes 1-2 days depending on size and complexity. Whole-property drylining can take 1-2 weeks. We will give you a clear timeline during your quote.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">Is drylining cheaper than traditional plastering?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">Drylining is generally more cost-effective than wet plastering for large areas. It requires less drying time, less labour, and produces minimal mess.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">Can drylining include insulation?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">Yes. We install insulation-backed plasterboard to improve thermal performance and meet Part L building regulations.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">Do you provide a guarantee?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">Yes. All our drylining work comes with a 12-month workmanship guarantee. We also use manufacturer-guaranteed materials from British Gypsum and Knauf.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">Is drylining suitable for bathrooms?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">Yes, when moisture-resistant plasterboard is used. We also recommend appropriate tanking in high-moisture areas.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;background:var(--white);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px;color:var(--primary);">What areas do you cover?</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light);margin:0;">We provide drylining services across Edinburgh, Leith, Livingston, Dalkeith, Musselburgh, Falkirk, and all surrounding Lothians and Central Scotland areas.</p>
  </div>
</div>

</div></section>
